<TITLE> Eid-ul-Fitr begins Tuesday for most of Mideast </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 30 (bdnews24.com)  Eid-ul-Fitr festivities, marking the end of Ramadan, will be celebrated from Tuesday in Saudi Arabia, Lebanon, Libya and Jordan, AFP reports. Religious authorities in Saudi Arabia, home to Islam's holiest shrines, said the Shawal moon had been sighted Monday, ending the month of fasting. Lebanon and Jordan made similar announcements. The Islamic calendar is a lunar one, and most Muslim countries set the beginning of Eid-ul-Fitr by the sighting of the new moon. But Libya -- where the celebrations also begin on Tuesday -- uses astronomical calculations. Kuwait, Qatar and the United Arab Emirates followed Saudi Arabia. In Egypt, however, state television announced Eid will be celebrated on Wednesday. bd
